## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-103">Uma <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> difere de um <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> em que os dados são armazenados no servidor, em vez de em um arquivo físico no sistema operacional.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-103">An <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> differs from an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile> in that the data is stored on the server instead of in a physical file in the operating system.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-104">Ele também pode ser um objeto de leitura / gravação, ao contrário de um <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile>, que é sempre somente leitura.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-104">It can also be a read-write object, unlike an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleBFile>, which is always read-only.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-105">Uma <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> pode ser uma das seguintes <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleType> tipos de dados.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-105">An <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> may be one of these <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleType> data types.</span></span>  
  
|<span data-ttu-id="ec21c-106">Tipo de dados de OracleType</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-106">OracleType data type</span></span>|<span data-ttu-id="ec21c-107">Descrição</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-107">Description</span></span>|  
|--------------------------|-----------------|  
|`Blob`|<span data-ttu-id="ec21c-108">Um Oracle `BLOB` tipo de dados que contém dados binários com um tamanho máximo de 4 gigabytes (GB).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-108">An Oracle `BLOB` data type that contains binary data with a maximum size of 4 gigabytes (GB).</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-109">Isso é mapeado para um <xref:System.Array> do tipo <xref:System.Byte>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-109">This maps to an <xref:System.Array> of type <xref:System.Byte>.</span></span>|  
|`Clob`|<span data-ttu-id="ec21c-110">Um Oracle `CLOB` tipo de dados que contém dados de caractere, com base no caractere padrão definido no servidor, com um tamanho máximo de 4 GB.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-110">An Oracle `CLOB` data type that contains character data, based on the default character set on the server, with a maximum size of 4 GB.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-111">Isso é mapeado para <xref:System.String>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-111">This maps to <xref:System.String>.</span></span>|  
|`NClob`|<span data-ttu-id="ec21c-112">Um Oracle `NCLOB` tipo de dados que contém dados de caractere, com base em conjunto no servidor com um tamanho máximo de 4 GB de caracteres nacional.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-112">An Oracle `NCLOB` data type that contains character data, based on the national character set on the server with a maximum size of 4 GB.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-113">Isso é mapeado para <xref:System.String>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-113">This maps to <xref:System.String>.</span></span>|  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-114">Um desenvolvedor de aplicativos .NET pode recuperar o Oracle `LOB` valores em tipos de dados .NET básicos, como <xref:System.Array> do tipo <xref:System.Byte> e <xref:System.String>, ou o especializado <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> tipo de dados.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-114">A .NET application developer can retrieve the Oracle `LOB` values into basic .NET data types, such as <xref:System.Array> of type <xref:System.Byte> and <xref:System.String>, or the specialized <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> data type.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-115">O <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> classe oferece suporte a dados de leitura e gravação para o Oracle `LOB` no banco de dados Oracle.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-115">The <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> class supports reading data from and writing to the Oracle `LOB` in the Oracle database.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-116">A seguir estão as principais características de um <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> tipo de dados que distingui-lo de tipos de dados básicos do .NET:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-116">The following are the main characteristics of an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> data type that distinguish it from basic .NET data types:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-117">Depois de recuperar o Oracle `LOB` valor do banco de dados Oracle para o <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> classe, você pode alterar o `LOB` dados em uma transação aberta e as alterações são refletidos diretamente ao banco de dados.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-117">After you retrieve the Oracle `LOB` value from the Oracle database into the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> class, you can change the `LOB` data in an open transaction and your changes are directly reflected to the database.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-118">Se você recuperar o Oracle `LOB` de valor em uma <xref:System.Array> do tipo <xref:System.Byte> ou <xref:System.String> e atualizar essas matrizes, suas alterações não serão refletidas no banco de dados.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-118">If you retrieve the Oracle `LOB` value into an <xref:System.Array> of type <xref:System.Byte> or <xref:System.String> and update these arrays, your changes are not reflected to the database.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-119">Quando você usa o <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> classe para acessar uma parte de um `LOB` valor, somente essa parte é passada do banco de dados Oracle para o cliente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-119">When you use the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> class to access a chunk of a `LOB` value, only that chunk is passed from the Oracle database to the client.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-120">Quando você usa o <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetChars%2A> método para acessar uma parte de um `LOB` valor, todo o conteúdo do valor é passado do banco de dados Oracle para o cliente.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-120">When you use the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetChars%2A> method to access a chunk of a `LOB` value, the entire contents of the value are passed from the Oracle database to the client.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-121">Para obter um <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> do objeto, chame o <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOracleLob%2A> método.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-121">To obtain an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> object, call the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader.GetOracleLob%2A> method.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-122">Você pode construir um <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> que é NULL usando este formato:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-122">You can construct an <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob> that is NULL using this format:</span></span>  
  
```  
OracleLob myLob = OracleLob.Null;  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-123">Essa técnica é usada principalmente para testar se um `LOB` retornada do servidor for NULL, como mostra este exemplo:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-123">This technique is used primarily to test whether a `LOB` returned from the server is NULL, as this example illustrates:</span></span>  
  
```  
If(myLob == OracleLob.Null)  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-124">Um valor nulo `LOB` se comporta da mesma forma para zero bytes `LOB` em que <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob.Read%2A> é bem-sucedida e sempre retorna zero bytes.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-124">A NULL `LOB` behaves similarly to a zero-byte `LOB` in that <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob.Read%2A> succeeds and always returns zero bytes.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-125">Selecionando uma `LOB` coluna que contém um valor nulo retorna <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob.Null>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-125">Selecting a `LOB` column that contains a null value returns <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob.Null>.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-126">Você deve iniciar uma transação antes de obter um temporário `LOB`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-126">You must begin a transaction before obtaining a temporary `LOB`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-127">Caso contrário, o <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader> poderá não conseguir obter os dados mais tarde.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-127">Otherwise, the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleDataReader> may fail to obtain data later.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-128">Você também pode abrir um temporário `LOB` no Oracle, chamando o DBMS_LOB. Sistema CREATETEMPORARY procedimento armazenado e associação de um `LOB` parâmetro de saída.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-128">You can also open a temporary `LOB` in Oracle by calling the DBMS_LOB.CREATETEMPORARY system stored procedure and binding a `LOB` output parameter.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-129">No lado do cliente, um temporário `LOB` se comporta como uma tabela com base em `LOB`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-129">On the client side, a temporary `LOB` behaves like a table-based `LOB`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-130">Por exemplo, para atualizar temporárias `LOB`, ele deve ser incluído em uma transação.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-130">For example, to update the temporary `LOB`, it must be enclosed in a transaction.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-131">O exemplo c# a seguir demonstra como abrir um temporário `LOB`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-131">The following C# example demonstrates how to open a temporary `LOB`.</span></span>  
  
```  
OracleConnection connection = new OracleConnection("server=MyServer; integrated security=yes;");  
connection.Open();  
OracleTransaction transaction = connection.BeginTransaction();  
OracleCommand command = connection.CreateCommand();  
command.Transaction = transaction;  
command.CommandText = "declare xx blob; begin dbms_lob.createtemporary(xx, false, 0); :tempblob := xx; end;";  
command.Parameters.Add(new OracleParameter("tempblob", OracleType.Blob)).Direction = ParameterDirection.Output;  
command.ExecuteNonQuery();  
OracleLob tempLob = (OracleLob)command.Parameters[0].Value;  
byte[] tempbuff = new byte[10000];  
tempLob.BeginBatch(OracleLobOpenMode.ReadWrite);  
tempLob.Write(tempbuff,0,tempbuff.Length);  
tempLob.EndBatch();  
command.Parameters.Clear();  
command.CommandText = "MyTable.MyProc";  
command.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure;    
command.Parameters.Add(new OracleParameter("ImportDoc", OracleType.Blob)).Value = tempLob;  
command.ExecuteNonQuery();  
transaction.Commit();  
connection.Close  
```  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-132">O herdadas <xref:System.IO.Stream.WriteByte%2A> método falhará se usado com dados de caractere e um <xref:System.InvalidOperationException> é gerada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-132">The inherited <xref:System.IO.Stream.WriteByte%2A> method fails if used with character data, and an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException> is thrown.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-133">Use o método <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob.Write%2A> em seu lugar.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-133">Use the <xref:System.Data.OracleClient.OracleLob.Write%2A> method instead.</span></span>  
>   
>  <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-134">Temporário `LOB`s são somente fechado quando a conexão for fechada, mas com o pool e sob carga, temporária `LOB`s não fechar.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-134">Temporary `LOB`s are only closed when the connection is closed, but with pooling and under load, temporary `LOB`s do not close.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-135">Isso pode ser resolvido removendo temporários `LOB`, invocando `tempLob.Dispose()`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-135">This can be resolved by disposing the temporary `LOB`, by invoking `tempLob.Dispose()`.</span></span>

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="ec21c-308">O exemplo a seguir demonstra como criar um temporário `LOB`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="ec21c-308">The following example demonstrates how to create a temporary `LOB`.</span></span>  
  
```  
OracleConnection connection = new OracleConnection("server=MyServer; integrated security=yes;");  
connection.Open();  
